frameDefinitions: A Protagonist is described as being exposed to a potentially dangerous situation that may end in a Bad_outcome for him- or herself.
This frame is concerned with the likelihood of a Hypothetical_event occurring.
A particular Situation is likely (or unlikely) to result in a harmful event befalling an Asset.
An Agent has a choice of whether or not to participate in some Desirable_event because of an Opportunity, a situation not completely under the Agent's control and usually of a limited duration.
The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.
frameExamples: It is <t>likely</t> that he'll arrive late.
It would be pleasant in the <t>opportune</t> absence of the clergyman to have a dance . DNI
The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
listRoleDefinitions: The person who is at risk of some <fen>Bad_outcome</fen>
A situation that the <fen>Protagonist</fen> would like to avoid.
Something desirable possessed by or directly associated with the <fen>Protagonist</fen> which might be lost or damaged.
The <fen>Action</fen> that creates the risk.
The time when the risk pertains.
The place where there is risk.
The state of affairs or occurrence whose likelihood is assessed.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Situation</fen> which may lead to a harmful event.
Something judged to be desirable or valuable which might be lost or damaged.
A concrete or abstract entity which may come to cause the loss of, or damage to the Asset.
The time period during which the <fen>Situation</fen> has the specified level of safety.
A particular location for which the <fen>Situation</fen> is safe. Frequently, it is to be inferred that the characteristics of the location make various <fen>Situation</fen>s safe or unsafe.
The situation during which the <fen>Desirable_situation</fen> is possible. For nominal LUs, this is generally in the second layer and contains the target.
The sentient agent that may or may not participate in the <fen>Desirable_situation</fen>.
A situation or event that the <fen>Agent</fen> can participating in during the period of the <fen>Opportunity</fen>.
The undesirable event which occurs.
The entity that experiences the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen>.
When the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> takes place.
listRoleExamples: There was no risk <fex>of his returning</fex>.
The risk <fex>to his reputation</fex> was significant.
<fex>Implementing this program</fex> runs the risk of offending our core constituents.
<fex>Even after the end of Apartheit</fex> we still run the risk of letting racism continue forever.
There is always some danger to rich men <fex>in a bar like this</fex>.
<fex>Rain</fex> is fairly unlikely today, I think.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>today</fex>.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>in Seattle</fex>.
Most people agree, <fex>going over 100mph</fex> is unsafe.
An <fex>environmental</fex> disaster is just what we need.
